Privacy Policy for StoreShot
Last Updated: April 19, 2026

1. Introduction
StoreShot ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our Chrome Extension.

2. Information We Collect
To provide our services, we only collect the minimum amount of data necessary:

Identity Information: Your email address (collected via Gumroad) for premium license management.

Authentication Information: Your license key to verify and activate premium features.

Technical Data: Basic extension settings (e.g., your preferred device frames or background colors) which are stored locally in your browser.

3. Image Processing (The "Local-First" Rule)
Your privacy is our priority. * All image processing, mockup generation, and canvas rendering happen locally on your computer.

We do NOT upload, store, or transmit your screenshots, images, or app data to any remote server. * Once you close the extension or download your image, the temporary data used for rendering is cleared.

4. Data Usage
We use the collected information solely to:

Verify your "Premium" status.

Provide customer support and license recovery.

Save your UI preferences within the extension so you don't have to reset them each time.

5. Third-Party Services
We use Gumroad as our payment processor. When you purchase a license, your financial information (credit card, billing address) is handled exclusively by Gumroad. You can view their privacy policy on their official website.

6. Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your local storage data and license information. We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.

